=begin pod
=head2 clear-slist

Clears a pointer to a B<Gnome::Glib::N-SList>, freeing it and, optionally, freeing its elements using C<$destroy>.
 C<$slist_ptr> must be a valid pointer. If C<$slist_ptr> points to a null B<Gnome::Glib::N-SList>, this does nothing.

=begin code
method clear-slist ( N-SList() $slist-ptr, &destroy )
=end code

=item $slist-ptr; a B<Gnome::Glib::N-SList> return location.
=item &destroy; the function to pass to g_slist_free_full() or undefined to not free elements. Tthe function must be specified with following signature; C<:( gpointer $data )>.

